Description:
PatientMD is an Integrated Mobile Platform for information sharing and healthcare services. Our focus is to move the healthcare to a Patient-Centered Value-Based industry providing Precision Medicine and Personalized Healthcare. We have built 3 commercial apps on our platform for: Patients, Doctors and healthcare businesses. Our fourth app is used internally for our sales and customer support team.
The foundation of our platform is our Patient Personal Health Record (PHR) and our interoperable consolidated Electronic Health Record (EHR) built on the FHIR protocol that can also interoperate with existing EHRs. We have built a number of services and technologies that utilize the data in our PHR, such as: Genomics (sequencing and biomarker identification), Artificial Intelligence, IoT, Telemedicine, Healthcare Services Marketplace, Healthcare Tourism and Appointment Scheduling. Our objective is to merge clinical, genomic and IoT data and use predictive analytics and AI to educate the patient and their doctor on Precision Medicine and Personalized Healthcare. As patients become engaged and empowered, they can then utilize our Marketplace for purchasing the desired services where price and quality transparency exists, creating an Amazon like experience. Patients can also use our Healthcare Tourism section to search domestically or internationally for the services. Patients will be rewarded/incentivized to earn our “Patient” token based on good behavior either medical or economical.
We're looking for a highly-motivated, self-starting DevOps Engineer that is excited to learn new cloud technologies and languages.
In this role, you will engage directly with the project team to create functionally rich and intuitive web-based and native mobile applications for PatientMD. You will work closely with business domain subject matter experts, software requirements analysts, software quality engineers, and developers to plan and test PatientMD Apps and WebApps. In addition, you will become part of the team that fosters the sharing and application of knowledge regarding current and emerging state-of-the-market software technologies.
The ideal candidate has a passion for technology, teamwork and collaboration, and continuous improvement of key processes.
Specific responsibilities include:
* Lead the build out of automated testing capabilities with existing continuous integration practices;
* Create test plans and test cases for assigned component/feature in coordination with Product Owners and Development Team;
* Execute test cases and perform defect tracking and management;
* Contribute in building automated regression tests;
* Contribute to and lead continuous improvement of software quality assurance processes and resources;
* Test across a variety of web browsers and mobile device platforms;
* Maintain documentation of testing to assist in debugging software.
QUALIFICATIONS
* Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or equivalent;
* Minimum 0-2 years of experience;
* Experience with automation testing tools such as Selenium and SpecFlow;
* Experience writing automated tests in a behavior-driven development (BDD) style using Gherkin syntax;
* Ability to interpret requirements and translate them into precise test cases;
* Familiarity with test-driven development;
* Experience in security testing;
* Ability to convert/adapt scripts to include performance and scalability testing;
* Experience in testing enterprise-level integrated backend server applications (distributed systems);
* Knowledge of Web development frameworks, languages, and services, including Python, HTML, JavaScript, XML, JSON, and RESTful APIs;
* Strong writing and communication skills within a team environment;
* Mobile application testing experience for the iOS and/or Android platforms.
* Healthcare experience preferred
Job Type: Full-time
Experience:
Work: 3 years (Preferred)
Education:
Bachelor's (Preferred)
Location:
Kolkata, West Bengal (Preferred)

Overview:
THE COMPANY

Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. ("Axalta," or the "Company"), is a leading global manufacturer, marketer and distributor of high-performance coatings systems. With over a 150-year heritage in the coatings industry, Axalta is known for manufacturing high-quality products with well-recognized brands supported by market-leading technology and customer service.
Over the course of the Company's history, Axalta has remained at the forefront of the industry by continually developing innovative coatings technologies designed to enhance the performance and appearance of customers' products, while improving the customer's productivity and profitability. Axalta's diverse global footprint of 50 manufacturing facilities, four technology centers, 47 customer training centers and more than 14,000 team members allows the Company to meet the needs of customers in over 130 countries. Axalta serves its customer base through an extensive sales force and technical support organization, as well as through approximately 4,000 independent, locally-based distributors. The Company's scale and strong local presence are critical to its success, allowing leverage of the technology portfolio and customer relationships globally while meeting customer demands locally.
Axalta operates its business in two operating segments: Performance Coatings and Transportation Coatings, serving four end markets, including: Refinish, Industrial, Light Vehicle and Commercial Vehicle, across the following four regions: North America, EMEA, Latin America and Asia-Pacific.
Responsibilities:
The primary responsibility of this position is to analyze important data utilizing statistical tools. The data will come on a daily base from several sources around the globe. The data will then need to be evaluated and determined whether there is an impact to production. This role will make appropriate recommendations to our manufacturing networks. Also, the resulting statistical reports will be shared with different functions within Axalta throughout the world.

Gather data from different internal or external sources (like SAP, but also scanned documents) on a daily basis
Build up and/ or use appropriate database to store data;
Use statistical tools to analyze data for trend, abnormalities etc.;
Determine cause/effect and make recommendations to manufacturing network
Report findings in standardized reports back to Axalta functions and sites.
Qualifications:
BS degree or above in a mathematical or engineering discipline;
Detailed knowledge in the area of statistical data analysis;
Six sigma black belt certification would be beneficial;
Basic knowledge in chemistry would be beneficial;
Fluent oral and excellent written English skills;
Effective written and oral communication;
Team spirit, open-minded.
Problem solver
5+ years working in a chemical operation would be preferred

